Its alliance with MUFG also confirms how the current financial crisis forces Wall Street's biggest names to adopt a much more prudent attitude than the one previously assumed.
The modalities defined Monday also show that in the last days the agreement has been modified: last Monday, Morgan had simply announced the sale of 20% of its shares to the Japanese giant for an amount of $8.5 billion.
